(5, 'When to Consult a Nephrologist in India?', 'A nephrologist in Delhi, India is a medical practitioner specialized in examining the kidneys...', 'Nephrologist.avif', '<p style=\'text-align: justify;color: rgb(42, 42, 42);background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 21px;font-family: \"\'><span style=\"font-size: 22px;\">A <strong><a href=\"https://www.kidneytotalcareindia.com/\" style=\"color: rgb(51, 144, 240);font-size: 21px;border: none;\">nephrologist in Delhi</a>, India</strong> is a medical practitioner specialized in examining the kidneys and diagnosing the diseases related to them. &ldquo;Nephros&rdquo; is a Greek word which means kidney or renal, whereas, the term &ldquo;ologist&rdquo; refers to someone who studies the specific field of medical science. The Nephrologists complete their learning in internal medicine and then undergo a training session to enhance their skills to become a specialized doctor in diagnosing the kidney-related diseases. The common conditions that are examined and treated by the nephrologists are polycystic kidney disease (PKD), chronic kidney disease (CKD), kidney stones, acute renal failure, and high blood pressure. Some doctors also specialize in kidney transplantation and dialysis.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'text-align: justify;color: rgb(42, 42, 42);background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 21px;font-family: \"\'><span style=\"font-size: 22px;\">When to see a <strong><a href=\"https://www.kidneytotalcareindia.com/\" style=\"color: rgb(51, 144, 240);font-size: 21px;border: none;\">Kidney Specialist in Delhi</a></strong>?</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'text-align: justify;color: rgb(42, 42, 42);background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 21px;font-family: \"\'><span style=\"font-size: 22px;\">A person is said to be a candidate to consult a <a href=\"https://www.kidneytotalcareindia.com/\" style=\"color: rgb(51, 144, 240);font-size: 21px;border: none; \"><strong>kidney doctor in Delhi</strong></a> when he is experiencing or having:</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: disc;\">\r\n    <li style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Acute renal failure</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Augmented drop in kidney function</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Chronic kidney disease reached to stage 4 or 5</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Chronic urinary tract infections</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Frequent urinary tract infections even after certain medications</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-size: 20px;\">A Glomerular Filtration Rate (GFR) at a level of 30 or below</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Reoccurrence of kidney stones after the complete treatment</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-size: 20px;\">High blood pressure not responding to certain medications</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Blood clots in the urine</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Protein loss in the urine</li>\r\n</ul>', 'When to Consult a Nephrologist in India for Kidney Care', 'Know when to consult a nephrologist in India for kidney problems like chronic kidney disease, kidney stones, high blood pressure, and urinary tract infections. Early care can protect your kidney health.', 'nephrologist in india,\r\nkidney specialist in delhi,\r\nkidney care india, \r\nchronic kidney disease treatment, \r\nkidney stone specialist delhi, \r\ndialysis doctor in india, \r\nkidney transplant specialist delhi, \r\nacute renal failure treatment, \r\nhigh blood pressure kidney link, \r\nurinary tract infection specialist', '2024-09-25', '[\"Kidney specialist\", \"Kidney specialist in India\", \"nephrologist\", \"nephrologist in India\"]', '', 'when-to-consult-a-nephrologist-in-india'),
(6, 'Types of Kidney Disease Increasing the Risk of Kidney Failure', 'Acute kidney injury is the sudden impairment happened to the kidneys. Usually, the cases...', 'kidneyDiseases.jpeg', '<p style=\'text-align: justify;color: rgb(42, 42, 42);background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 21px;font-family: \"\'><strong><span style=\"font-size: 22px;\">Kidney disorders</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 22px;\"> are largely categorized into acute kidney injury and chronic <a href=\"https://www.kidneydrsunilprakash.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"dofollow\" style=\"color: rgb(51, 144, 240);font-size: 21px;border: none;\"><strong>kidney diseases</strong></a>.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'text-align: justify;color: rgb(42, 42, 42);background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 21px;font-family: \"\'><span style=\"font-size: 22px;\">Acute kidney injury is the sudden impairment happened to the kidneys. Usually, the cases are short-term based, but, in rare cases, the condition may last longer. The chief causes of acute kidney injury are:</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\'text-align: justify; color: rgb(42, 42, 42); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 14px; font-family: \"border: none;\"; list-style-type: disc;\'>\r\n    <li style=\"font-size: 20px; border: none;\">damage to the definite kidney tissue triggered by a severe infection, drug or radioactive dye</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-size: 20px; border: none;\">Blockage in urination due to kidney stones or an enlarged prostate, for example.</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-size: 20px; border: none;\">According to the best <strong><a href=\"https://www.kidneytotalcareindia.com/\" style=\"color: rgb(90, 90, 90);font-size: 14px;border: none;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Nephrologist in Delhi</span></a><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">,</span> India</strong> chronic kidney disease can also contribute to the risk of acute kidney injury.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\'text-align: justify;color: rgb(42, 42, 42);background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 21px;font-family: \"\'><span style=\"font-size: 22px;\">On the other hand, chronic <a href=\"https://www.drvinantbhargava.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"dofollow\" style=\"color: rgb(51, 144, 240);font-size: 21px;border: none;\"><strong>kidney disease</strong></a> occurs over several years of malfunctioning of the organ. Sometimes, it can lead to End-Stage Kidney Disease for which a patient is kept on dialysis or else suggested for a kidney transplant to live an active life. There are different factors that contribute to chronic kidney disease, these include:</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: disc;\">\r\n    <li style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Damaged blood vessels to the kidneys because of medical conditions like high blood pressure and diabetes</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Outbreaks of the kidney tissue due to a certain disease or weak immune system (glomerulonephritis)</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Progressing or growing cysts on the kidney, known as polycystic kidney disease)</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Destruction due to reverse flow of urine back into the kidneys. The condition is called reflux nephropathy.</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Congenital abnormalities of the urinary tract.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\'text-align: justify;color: rgb(42, 42, 42);background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 21px;font-family: \"\'><span style=\"font-size: 22px;\">According to healthcare professionals, if any time a person experiences or observes the signs and symptoms of chronic kidney disease (CKD), it is best to consult the <strong><a href=\"https://www.kidneytotalcareindia.com/\" style=\"color: rgb(51, 144, 240);font-size: 21px;border: none;\">best Nephrologist in Delhi</a>, India</strong> as soon as possible to prevent the condition from getting worse. Early diagnose and treatment of CKD can lower the risk of end-stage kidney failure. Knowing the body and consulting the <strong><a href=\"https://www.kidneytotalcareindia.com/\" style=\"color: rgb(51, 144, 240);font-size: 21px;border: none;\">kidney specialist in Delhi</a>, India</strong> is the best way to prevent severe <a href=\"https://www.drshailendragoel.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"dofollow\" style=\"color: rgb(51, 144, 240);font-size: 21px;border: none;\"><strong>kidney disorders</strong></a> in the future. The conditions may include:</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\'text-align: justify; color: rgb(42, 42, 42); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 14px; font-family: \"border: none;\"; list-style-type: disc;\'>\r\n    <li style=\"font-size: 20px; border: none;\">Blood in urine</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-size: 20px; border: none;\"><a href=\"https://www.kidneyhospitalstonecentre.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"dofollow\" style=\"color: rgb(90, 90, 90);font-size: 20px;border: none;\">Kidney stones</a></li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-size: 20px; border: none;\">Protein in urine</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-size: 20px; border: none;\">Acute kidney injury</li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-size: 20px; border: none;\">Kidney infection</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Types of Kidney Disease Increasing the Risk of Kidney Failure', 'Learn about different types of kidney disease, their causes, and how early diagnosis and treatment can prevent kidney failure. Consult the best nephrologist in Delhi, India for expert care.', 'kidney disease, \r\nacute kidney injury, \r\nchronic kidney disease,\r\nkidney failure risk,\r\nbest nephrologist in delhi, \r\nkidney specialist in india, \r\nkidney transplant in delhi,\r\ndialysis treatment delhi,\r\nkidney infection treatment,\r\nkidney care india', '2024-09-25', '[\"Kidney specialist\"]', '', 'types-of-kidney-disease-increasing-the-risk-of-kidney-failure'),
(7, 'Top Reasons to Visit the Best Nephrologist in India', 'A diagnosis of kidney problem means frequent doctor visits, lab tests, dialysis, change in diet and even kidney...', 'doctorpatient.jpg', '<p style=\'text-align: justify;color: rgb(42, 42, 42);background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 21px;font-family: \"\'><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">A diagnosis of kidney problem means frequent doctor visits, lab tests, dialysis, change in diet and even kidney transplant in the future. Diet and medications can hold these kidney problems if followed regularly. Listening to the advice of <strong><a href=\"https://www.kidneytotalcareindia.com/\" style=\"color: rgb(51, 144, 240);font-size: 21px;border: none;\">best nephrologist in Delhi</a></strong> is extremely important for a kidney patient at any stage of the disease. Early diagnosis of the problem can slow down the disease occurrence and even results in stoppage from advancing. Nothing can be done to cure the problem if it becomes more serious. <a href=\"https://www.kidneytotalcareindia.com/\" style=\"color: rgb(51, 144, 240);font-size: 21px;border: none;\"><strong>Nephrologist in Delhi</strong></a> plays an essential role in making decisions in relation to withholding or withdrawing treatment related to kidney patient.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'text-align: justify;color: rgb(42, 42, 42);background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 21px;font-family: \"\'><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Kidney infection is another main cause of kidney failure. If you are suffering from diabetes and experiencing urine problem it is advisable to visit <strong><a href=\"https://www.kidneytotalcareindia.com/\" style=\"color: rgb(51, 144, 240);font-size: 21px;border: none;\">kidney specialist in Delhi</a>, India.&nbsp;</strong>Diabetes causes damage to the small blood vessels. It also damages the nerves in the bladder causing pressure on the kidney. This results in either infection in the kidney or kidney failure. <strong><a href=\"https://www.kidneytotalcareindia.com/\" style=\"color: rgb(51, 144, 240);font-size: 21px;border: none;\">Best kidney specialist in Delhi</a>&nbsp;</strong>suggests the diabetic patient keep an eye on the symptoms. The most common symptoms are at a high level of protein in urine, swelling, itchiness, tiredness, and breathlessness. It is advisable to immediately visit the <strong>best kidney hospital in India&nbsp;</strong>to get the best treatment to cure this problem.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'text-align: justify;color: rgb(42, 42, 42);background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 21px;font-family: \"\'><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Early discovery of the disease can be lifesaving. Early detection of the problem can work the best to control the condition. But if the problem is in its last stage organ transplant is the only option left. This is the process carried out to place a healthy kidney in the body of the patient suffering from failure. Kidney transplantation by <strong><a href=\"https://www.kidneytotalcareindia.com/\" style=\"color: rgb(51, 144, 240);font-size: 21px;border: none;\">kidney doctor in Delhi</a></strong> offers improved value of life since it lets greater freedom and higher energy level than before. However, there are certain complications like the rejection of new kidney also occurs. To prevent these complications <strong><a href=\"https://www.kidneytotalcareindia.com/\" style=\"color: rgb(51, 144, 240);font-size: 21px;border: none;\">best&nbsp;nephrologist in Delhi</a>&nbsp;</strong>follow their patients regularly for a year after the surgery. If you are experiencing such symptoms or have any issues related to your kidney it is best advisable to have an immediate visit <strong>best nephrology hospital in India&nbsp;</strong>to get excellent treatment and happier years to your life.</span></p>', 'Top Reasons to Visit the Best Nephrologist in India for Kidney Care', 'Discover why consulting the best nephrologist in India is vital for early kidney disease detection, treatment, and long-term health, including expert care for dialysis and transplants.', 'best nephrologist in india,\r\nkidney specialist in delhi,\r\nkidney doctor in delhi,\r\nbest kidney hospital in india,\r\nnephrology treatment india,\r\ndialysis specialist delhi,\r\nkidney transplant in india,\r\nkidney care expert,\r\nnephrology hospital delhi,\r\nkidney disease treatment india', '2024-09-26', '[\"Kidney specialist\", \"nephrologists in India\", \"best Kidney specialist in Delhi\", \"best nephrologist in Delhi\", \"best nephrologist in India\", \"Kidney specialist in Delhi\", \"nephrologist in Delhi\", \"nephrologist in India\"]', '', 'best-nephrologist-in-delhi-india'),
(8, 'Kidney Transplant in India is a Finest Treatment Option for Kidney Failure', 'Gone are the days when kidney transplantation was a very rare treatment.  Today there are numerous hospitals...', 'KidneyTransplant.png', '<p style=\'text-align: justify;color: rgb(42, 42, 42);background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 21px;font-family: \"\'><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Gone are the days when kidney transplantation was a very rare treatment. Today there are numerous hospitals for a <strong><a href=\"https://www.kidneytotalcareindia.com/kidney-transplantation.html\" style=\"color: rgb(51, 144, 240);font-size: 21px;border: none;\">kidney transplant in Delhi</a>, India</strong> that have all facilities and qualified surgeons to do this procedure successfully. This process is putting a healthy kidney in the body of a person with end-stage renal disease. &nbsp;Three alternative treatments are usually available for the person having kidney problem -hemodialysis, peritoneal dialysis, and kidney transplantation.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'text-align: justify;color: rgb(42, 42, 42);background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 21px;font-family: \"\'><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">However transplantation is not a cure, it demands to have medications for the rest of life. Better strengths, power, and liveliness are the after-effects of a successful transplant. After the surgery, the patient will be able to return to a usual lifestyle with a normal diet and more fluid intake. Major reasons that lead to end-stage renal disease are &ndash;</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\'text-align: justify; color: rgb(42, 42, 42); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 14px; font-family: \"border: none;\"; list-style-type: disc;\'>\r\n    <li style=\"text-align: left; font-size: 22px; border: none;\">Urinary Infections</li>\r\n    <li style=\"text-align: left; font-size: 22px; border: none;\">Diabetes</li>\r\n    <li style=\"text-align: left; font-size: 22px; border: none;\">High Blood Pressure</li>\r\n    <li style=\"text-align: left; font-size: 22px; border: none;\">Inherited Disorders</li>\r\n    <li style=\"text-align: left; font-size: 22px; border: none;\">Immune System Diseases</li>\r\n    <li style=\"text-align: left; font-size: 22px; border: none;\">Hemolytic Uremic Syndrome</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\'text-align: justify;color: rgb(42, 42, 42);background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 21px;font-family: \"\'><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Starting on the difficult and extremely emotive journey to a life-saving transplant, it is highly difficult to decide where to start from. Following points should be kept in mind to choose <strong><a href=\"https://www.kidneytotalcareindia.com/\" style=\"color: rgb(51, 144, 240);font-size: 21px;border: none;\">best hospital for kidney transplant in Delhi</a>, India</strong> &ndash;</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\'text-align: justify; color: rgb(42, 42, 42); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 14px; font-family: \"border: none;\"; list-style-type: disc;\'>\r\n    <li style=\"text-align: left; font-size: 22px; border: none;\">Ask your <a href=\"https://www.kidneytotalcareindia.com/\" style=\"color: rgb(90, 90, 90);font-size: 14px;border: none;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 22px;\">kidney doctor in Delhi</span></strong></a></li>\r\n    <li style=\"text-align: left; font-size: 22px; border: none;\">Learn about the facts of the center</li>\r\n    <li style=\"text-align: left; font-size: 22px; border: none;\">Explore as many centers</li>\r\n    <li style=\"text-align: left; font-size: 22px; border: none;\">Search online</li>\r\n    <li style=\"text-align: left; font-size: 22px; border: none;\">Narrow down your list with 2 &ndash; 3 centers having high success rates and shorter wait time.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\'text-align: justify;color: rgb(42, 42, 42);background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 21px;font-family: \"\'><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Usually, there are no signs and symptoms that indicate the failure of a kidney. The most obvious systems appear only when the condition gets severe. Kidney failure sometimes causes fluid retention. Frequency and urgency of urination, vomiting, nausea, pale skin, loss of appetite are some usual signs. General kidney diseases can be treated by controlling the above situations, but for last stage disease, a kidney transplant is the only option.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'text-align: justify;color: rgb(42, 42, 42);background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);font-size: 21px;font-family: \"\'><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Kidney failure can greatly influence the normal working of the body. Harmful wastes may build up, blood pressure may rise considerably, and body retains excess fluid and will not be able to build enough red blood cells. <strong><a href=\"https://www.kidneytotalcareindia.com/kidney-transplantation.html\" style=\"color: rgb(51, 144, 240);font-size: 21px;border: none;\">Kidney transplant in India</a></strong> is considered as the finest treatment. A successful transplant needs close follow-up with the <strong><a href=\"https://www.kidneytotalcareindia.com/\" style=\"color: rgb(51, 144, 240);font-size: 21px;border: none;\">kidney doctor in Delhi</a>, India</strong> and taking proper medicines after the surgery to live a healthy life.</span></p>', 'Kidney Transplant in New Delhi – Best Treatment for Kidney Failure by Dr. Sunil Prakash', 'Kidney transplant in new delhi offers a life-saving solution for end-stage kidney failure. Get expert care from Dr. Sunil Prakash, top kidney specialist in Delhi, with high success rates and advanced facilities.', 'kidney transplant in India, \r\nbest kidney transplant hospital Delhi, kidney specialist in Delhi, \r\nend-stage renal disease treatment, \r\nkidney failure doctor India, \r\ndialysis vs transplant, \r\nchronic kidney disease surgery, \r\ntop nephrologist India, \r\nkidney transplant cost India, \r\nrenal replacement therapy', '2024-09-26', '[\"best kidney transplant in India\", \"Kidney transplant clinic in India\", \"Kidney transplant in India\", \"top Kidney in India\"]', '', 'kidney-transplant-in-india-is-a-finest-treatment-option-for-kidney-failure'),
